# Tethered Photography via Wired LAN (Ethernet)

Connect to wired LANs (Ethernet networks) for tethered photography using network computers.

1. Connect to the network by plugging an Ethernet cable into the cameraâ€™s LAN connector.

2. Select **CREATE/EDIT CONNECTION SETTING** > **CREATE USING WIZARD** in the network/USB setting menu and choose **TETHERED SHOOTING**.

3. Select **CREATE NEW**.

   !Tether Shooting Menu

   > ðŸ’¡ **Tip:**  
   > Choose **SELECT FROM LIST** to select from a list of existing connection setting profiles.

4. Press **MENU/OK** when prompted.

   !Select Comm Setting

5. Select **WIRED LAN**.

   !Wired LAN Selection
